PROGRAM 3

AWS IAM User and Permission Management

Aim
To manage users groups and permissions using IAM.

Step 1 Open IAM

1. Open AWS Console.
2. Search IAM.
3. Open IAM service.

Step 2 Open Users

1. Click Users from left panel.
2. Observe users user 1 user 2 and user 3.

Step 3 Open User Groups

1. Click User Groups.
2. Observe groups EC2 Admin EC2 Support and S3 Support.

Step 4 Add Users To Groups
Add user 1 to S3 Support

1. Open S3 Support.
2. Open Users tab.
3. Click Add users.
4. Select user 1.
5. Click Add users.

Add user 2 to EC2 Support
Repeat same steps.

Add user 3 to EC2 Admin
Repeat same steps.

Step 5 Test Users

1. Open Dashboard.
2. Copy IAM Sign In URL.
3. Open Incognito window.
4. Login with user 1 and verify S3 access.
5. Login with user 2 and verify EC2 Read Only access.
6. Login with user 3 and verify EC2 admin access.

Result
IAM users and permissions configured successfully.

